    },
    "Once the second note starts playing, the **Higher** and **Lower** buttons become active. Tap the one that matches what you heard." : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Sobald der zweite Ton zu spielen beginnt, werden die Tasten **Höher** und **Tiefer** aktiv. Tippe auf die Taste, die zu dem passt, was du gehört hast."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Peach" : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Peach"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Peach helps you train your ear for music. Practice hearing the difference between notes and learn to match pitches accurately." : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Peach hilft dir, dein Gehör für Musik zu trainieren. Übe, Unterschiede zwischen Tönen zu hören und Tonhöhen genau zu treffen."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Peach Training Data" : {
      "comment" : "The default preview title for a ShareLink that exports training data as a CSV file.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true,
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Peach-Trainingsdaten"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Perfect Fifth" : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Reine Quinte"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Perfect Fourth" : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Reine Quarte"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Piano sounds from [FluidR3_GM by Frank Wen](https://member.keymusician.com/Member/FluidR3_GM/index.html) (MIT License). All other sounds from [GeneralUser GS by S. Christian Collins](https://schristiancollins.com/generaluser.php)." : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Pianoklänge von [FluidR3_GM von Frank Wen](https://member.keymusician.com/Member/FluidR3_GM/index.html) (MIT-Lizenz). Alle anderen Klänge von [GeneralUser GS von S. Christian Collins](https://schristiancollins.com/generaluser.php)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Pick the **sound** you want to train with — each instrument has a different character.\n\n**Duration** controls how long each note plays.\n\n**Concert Pitch** sets the reference tuning. Most musicians use 440 Hz. Some orchestras tune to 442 Hz.\n\n**Tuning System** determines how intervals are calculated. Equal Temperament divides the octave into 12 equal steps and is standard for most Western music. Just Intonation uses pure frequency ratios and sounds smoother for some intervals." : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Wähle den **Klang**, mit dem du trainieren möchtest — jedes Instrument hat einen eigenen Charakter.\n\n**Dauer** bestimmt, wie lange jeder Ton gespielt wird.\n\n**Kammerton** legt die Referenzstimmung fest. Die meisten Musiker verwenden 440 Hz. Manche Orchester stimmen auf 442 Hz.\n\n**Stimmung** bestimmt, wie Intervalle berechnet werden. Die gleichstufige Stimmung teilt die Oktave in 12 gleiche Schritte und ist Standard in der westlichen Musik. Die reine Stimmung verwendet ganzzahlige Frequenzverhältnisse und klingt bei manchen Intervallen harmonischer."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Pitch adjustment slider" : {
      "localizations" : {
        "de" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "Tonhöhenregler"
          }
        }
      }
